    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.49-51_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">101</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">49</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 24, 1958.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Through our daughter, Edwyna, we have learned of your recent sorrow. We wish to extend to you, and to your family our sincere compassion.</p>
                
                <p>Although we are complete strangers to you, you are someone who has become very real, and very special to us.</p>
                
                <p>Edwyna has written, and spoken, to us of you and of Mrs. Neihardt with deepest admiration. To her,
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.49-51_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">50</fw>
                
                    you have been a great inspiration. Not only the beauty of your poetry &#8212; but the poetry of your living has made a lasting impression upon her. What a wonderful thing to have given, to even our young girl, so much of the fine and good!</p>
                
                <p>Thank you for all you have meant to her. We know that one who gives so much can know only the deepest peace.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>The Condons</signed>
                    <signed>(Mrs. Edw. V. Condon)</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
